abstract: The SoftBank founder said that investing his $93 billion tech fund shouldn’t be a problem — and has private equity moguls pondering their own giant funds.
snippet: The SoftBank founder said that investing his $93 billion tech fund shouldn’t be a problem — and has private equity moguls pondering their own giant funds.
lead_paragraph: Good Thursday morning from Andrew Ross Sorkin, who is flying back from Saudi Arabia, and Michael J. de la Merced and Amie Tsang in London. We’re thinking about Masayoshi Son’s comment to Andrew that $100 billion isn’t enough for his tech-investing ambitions. More on that in a minute.

abstract: Colony Capital will no longer provide an immediate financial lifeline, people briefed on the matter said, but the troubled studio still has other options.
snippet: Colony Capital will no longer provide an immediate financial lifeline, people briefed on the matter said, but the troubled studio still has other options.
lead_paragraph: The Weinstein Company is looking for a new financial lifeline after a preliminary agreement for an immediate cash infusion from Colony Capital fell through.

abstract: The Carlyle Group’s succession planning is part of a generational change at private equity firms, as the billionaires who pioneered the industry retire.
snippet: The Carlyle Group’s succession planning is part of a generational change at private equity firms, as the billionaires who pioneered the industry retire.
lead_paragraph: It started with a series of meetings at the Carlyle Hotel in New York, and grew to become one of the world’s most ambitious and well-connected private equity firms. Its Rolodex was unrivaled, and its advisers included the first President George Bush and John Major, the former British prime minister.

abstract: The Consumer Financial Protection Bureau’s proposed rule was defeated by an intense lobbying effort and moves by Republican allies in Congress.
snippet: The Consumer Financial Protection Bureau’s proposed rule was defeated by an intense lobbying effort and moves by Republican allies in Congress.
lead_paragraph: Good Wednesday morning from Andrew Ross Sorkin in Riyadh, Saudi Arabia, and Michael J. de la Merced and Amie Tsang in London. We’re watching the unlikely career resurrection of Klaus Kleinfeld, who will oversee a $500 billion economic development zone in Saudi Arabia. More on that in a moment.

abstract: Business leaders like Steve Schwarzman and Larry Fink are in attendance at Saudi Arabia’s Vision 2030 conference to see and be seen.
snippet: Business leaders like Steve Schwarzman and Larry Fink are in attendance at Saudi Arabia’s Vision 2030 conference to see and be seen.
lead_paragraph: Good Tuesday morning from Andrew Ross Sorkin in Riyadh, Saudi Arabia, and Michael J. de la Merced and Amie Tsang in London. We’re thinking about how President Trump’s sudden and unpredictable changes on policy positions could be harming Republicans’ tax overhaul efforts. More on that in a moment.

abstract: It’s astonishing to have named the tyrant a good-will ambassador, but the agency does vital work.
snippet: It’s astonishing to have named the tyrant a good-will ambassador, but the agency does vital work.
lead_paragraph: It is astonishing that Tedros Adhanom Ghebreyesus, the director general of the World Health Organization, picked Robert Mugabe as a “good-will ambassador.” After the inevitable outcry that followed, Dr. Tedros rescinded the nomination, but the question endures: Could the director general of a major United Nations agency, an Ethiopian who has held a variety of high-level posts in his country and abroad and is well respected in the field of public health, not have read reports on the damage the tyrant of Zimbabwe has done to his own country’s health system?

abstract: Starting late next month, electronic cigarettes will be banned from indoor public spaces like bars, restaurants and offices in New York State.
snippet: Starting late next month, electronic cigarettes will be banned from indoor public spaces like bars, restaurants and offices in New York State.
lead_paragraph: Electronic cigarettes, the popular vapor substitute to traditional tobacco cigarettes, will soon be banned from public indoor spaces in New York State — just like the real thing.

abstract: The oil giant’s chief executive denied that the company’s forthcoming stock sale faced delays, but gave few details of what the offering would look like.
snippet: The oil giant’s chief executive denied that the company’s forthcoming stock sale faced delays, but gave few details of what the offering would look like.
lead_paragraph: Good Monday morning from Andrew Ross Sorkin in Riyadh, Saudi Arabia, and Michael J. de la Merced and Amie Tsang in London. Andrew spent Sunday in Dhahran taping a television interview for CNBC at Saudi Aramco’s headquarters with its C.E.O. ahead of the kingdom’s Future of Finance Initiative — known informally as Davos in the Desert — that starts Tuesday morning.

abstract: A new crop of mega-philanthropists — from Soros to Gates to Koch — eclipses old guard, changes the rules and courts controversy.
snippet: A new crop of mega-philanthropists — from Soros to Gates to Koch — eclipses old guard, changes the rules and courts controversy.
lead_paragraph: Step aside, Rockefeller. Move over, Carnegie. Out of the way, Ford.
